https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/csharp-package-cli.html

dotnet new -i Amazon.Lambda.Templates
dotnet new lambda.EmptyFunction --name MyFunction

dotnet lambda deploy-function
dotnet lambda deploy-function MyFunction

dotnet lambda invoke-function MyFunction \
  --cli-binary-format raw-in-base64-out \
  --payload "Just Checking If Everything is OK"

The following does not work because the lambda expect a json
aws lambda invoke \
  --function-name MyFunction \
  --payload "Just Checking If Everything is OK" \
  /dev/stdout


Clean up
aws logs delete-log-group --log-group-name /aws/lambda/MyFunction
aws lambda delete-function --function-name MyFunction
It is easier just go to the aws console to delete the role associated to the lamdba